Customize Labels and Translations for the Channel Menu
Create Channel Menu Code Settings

To set up Channel Menu Code Settings, add optional JavaScript code as a static resource. This allows you to easily change the customer experience with a few clicks.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Channel Menu setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Channel Menu:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata
To set up Code Settings:	Author Apex

Code Settings are useful to add modifications to menu items. To change an image or pass routine information to pre-chat fields or to populate a hidden field, create static resource files and then upload them to Salesforce.

Create a Snippet Settings File with JavaScript

You can use your JavaScript static resource files, including strings, arrays, JSON, and JS functions for the Channel Menu. Use the supported settings:

Pre-chat and entity creations
Add extra pre-chat information or populate form fields to prepare agents for the customer conversation.
	prepopulatedPrechatFields
	extraPrechatInfo
	extraPrechatFormDetails

Branding
Customize your menu branding to maintain consistency and update changes easily.
	prechatBackgroundImgURL
	smallCompanyLogoImgURL
	waitingStateBackgroundImgURL
	chatbotAvatarImgURL
	avatarImgURL

Routing
Add routing to direct customer conversations to the right agent.
	directToButtonRouting
	fallbackRouting

SETTINGS TO MODIFY	SETTING NAME FOR MESSAGING FOR WEB CHANNEL

Messaging for Web
Turn on Messaging for Web developer mode to load unminified versions of static files and allow more logging to the developer console for troubleshooting.

Upload Your File to Static Resources
With your code ready, upload your file as a static resource in Setup (instructions for embedded resources).

Add Resources to Code Settings
Select Add Code Setting.
Type a unique Code Setting Name for your customization in the first field.
Add optional text in the Description box and detail the configuration.
From the Type pull-down menu, select a resource type.
Locate your uploaded resource name in the Static Resource box.

Save your changes.

For Salesforce Experience Cloud sites, skip the next code snippet steps. Instead, add the name in the property editor and load the Code Setting Name for your site on a specific page.

Open the code snippet that you added to the website.
Add the new parameter as an object to the embedded_svc.menu.init() call in the snippet.
Verify that your code snippet changes in your web page markup.
Refresh your web page and confirm that the Channel Menu button appears.
title: Customizing Salesforce Service Cloud Channel Menu
